        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/32/3/471/598",
        "text": [
          "٤٧١. وَقَالَ (عليه ‏السلام): لَا خَيْرَ فِي الصَّمْتِ عَنِ الْحُكْمِ، كَمَا أنَّهُ لَا خَيْرَ فِي الْقَوْلِ بِالْجَهْلِ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-ali-raza": [
            "471. Amīr al-mu’minīn, peace be upon him, said: There is no good in silence over matters involving wisdom just as there is no good in speaking with ignorance."
          ]
        }
      }
